#: ../../faq/faq_font_size.rst:4
msgid ":index:`How do I change the fonts size or font? <change font size>`"
msgstr ""
":index:`Hoe verander ik het lettertype en de grootte van de letters? "
"<lettergrootte wijzigen>`"

#: ../../faq/faq_font_size.rst:7
msgid "General"
msgstr "Algemeen"

#: ../../faq/faq_font_size.rst:9
msgid ""
"Picard is a Qt application, so whatever works for other Qt application will "
"work for Picard."
msgstr ""
"Picard is een Qt-applicatie, dus wat voor andere Qt-applicaties werkt, werkt "
"ook voor Picard."

#: ../../faq/faq_font_size.rst:12
msgid "Linux specific"
msgstr "Voor Linux"

#: ../../faq/faq_font_size.rst:15
msgid "Two ways to change the size/scaling are:"
msgstr "De grootte/schaal kan op twee manieren worden gewijzigd:"

#: ../../faq/faq_font_size.rst:17
msgid "**Desktop Settings**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../faq/faq_font_size.rst:0
msgid ""
"The usual default way to change the scaling is to rely on the settings of "
"the desktop environment, e.g. on GNOME the scaling set when configuring the "
"screens. This usually works, and should be the first approach to take."
msgstr ""
"De gebruikelijke manier is om de schaalinstellingen van de "
"bureaubladomgeving te gebruiken. In Gnome doe je dat bij de "
"schermconfiguratie. Meestal werkt dit, dus dit zou je als eerste moeten "
"proberen."

#: ../../faq/faq_font_size.rst:21
msgid "**Environment Settings**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../faq/faq_font_size.rst:0
msgid ""
"Setting the environment variable ``QT_SCALE_FACTOR`` will scale fonts for Qt "
"applications. This can be useful on 4k monitors. From a terminal, you can "
"then run ``QT_SCALE_FACTOR=2.0 picard`` to start Picard, or create an alias "
"in your shell, or set the variable in your shell to affect all Qt "
"applications."
msgstr ""
"Je kan ook de omgevingsvariabele ``QT_SCALE_FACTOR`` instellen om de "
"lettertypen in Qt-applicaties te schalen. Dit kan handig zijn voor 4K-"
"beeldschermen. Vervolgens kan je vanuit de terminal ``QT_SCALE_FACTOR=2.0 "
"picard`` uitvoeren om Picard te starten, een alias in je shell maken of de "
"variabele in je shell voor alle Qt-applicaties instellen."

#: ../../faq/faq_font_size.rst:25
msgid ""
"To change both the size/scaling and the font, use `qt5ct <https://"
"sourceforge.net/projects/qt5ct/>`_ to set the new font and/or size. Note "
"that these changes will apply to all Qt applications, not just Picard."
msgstr ""

#: ../../faq/faq_font_size.rst:27
msgid ""
"`The official documentation on high DPI <https://doc.qt.io/archives/qt-5.15/"
"highdpi.html>`_ could be a useful read as well."
msgstr ""
